Soviet paradise: concrete city built in the middle of the deep north, attached to a factory, neverending winter, polar lights hidden behind chimney smoke, all entertainment consists of drinking coffee and listening to radio - deep below the streets, unknown caverns gaping evil

Soviet project was about making "as below so above", buildings connected as large networks of stone, cave-like apartments, people pale from a lack of sun like Lovecraft's underground penguins, life indistinguishable from that in the depths of the earth

November forests are empty, snakes and squirrels sleep, bears hibernating, wolves not frenzied yet, most greens withered, tree leaves gone, insects gone, no snow, only wind - it's as if there was a smoke break between lectures and you remained in the room instead. Empty waiting.
